==English==

===Transitive verb===
'''to smash''', '''smashing''', '''smashed'''

# To damage or destroy by strong, blunt pressure.
#: ''The cans were slowly smashed flat under the wheel of the steamroller.''
# To break violently
#: ''The flying rock smashed the window to pieces.''
# To destroy completely and suddenly.
#: ''The news smashed any hopes of a reunion.''
# To defeat overwhelmingly.
#: ''The Indians smashed the Yankees 22-0.''

